ported:\u00a0Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cTake care of your Hereafter and Allah will take care of your worldly life. Take care of your private life and Allah will take care of your public life.\u201d Source:\u00a0Kita\u0304b al-Ikhla\u0304s\u0323 50 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0646\u064a\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19870,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/09\/19\/umar-on-secrecy\/","url_meta":{"origin":37441,"position":1},"title":"Umar on II Secrecy: Beware secret religious cults of misguidance","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 19, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Awza\u2019i reported: Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cIf you see people meeting in secret for their religion to the exclusion of the public, then know that they are establishing misguidance.\u201d Source: H\u0323ilyat al-Awliya\u0304' 5\/388 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0632\u064e\u0627\u0639\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0632\u0650\u064a\u0632\u0650 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23932,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/10\/27\/umar-ii-curses-becomes-worse\/","url_meta":{"origin":37441,"position":2},"title":"Umar II on Curses: He curses his oppressor until he is even worse","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 27, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Ribah ibn 'Ubaydah reported: I was sitting with Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, when the ruler Al-Hajjaj was mentioned, so I reviled and denounced him. Umar said, \u201cCalm down, O Ribah! Verily, I have heard that a man might be oppressed with a great wrong,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27156,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/02\/07\/umar-sabr-reward-better\/","url_meta":{"origin":37441,"position":3},"title":"Umar II on Sabr: Reward of patience better than material blessings","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 7, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn Amr reported: Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, said upon the pulpit, \u201cAllah does not grant a servant a blessing and then removes the blessing, then compensates him with patience in place of what was removed, but that what he was granted is better\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34608,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/11\/30\/umar-ii-humility-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":37441,"position":4},"title":"Umar II on Humility: Best Muslims are humble with Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 30, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Ghazali reported: Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cThe best people are those who are humble before Allah.\u201d Source: Ih\u0323ya\u0304\u2019 Ulu\u0304m al-Di\u0304n 3\/355 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u063a\u0632\u0627\u0644\u064a \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0632\u0650\u064a\u0632\u0650 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u062e\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0639\u0650\u0646\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0645\u064f\u062a\u064e\u0648\u064e\u0627\u0636\u0650\u0639\u064b\u0627 3\/355 \u0625\u062d\u064a\u0627\u0621 \u0639\u0644\u0648\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0646","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3657,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/13\/umar-ibn-abdul-aziz-islam\/","url_meta":{"origin":37441,"position":5},"title":"Umar II on Faith: Islam is fulfilled by duties, limits, traditions","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 13, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Bukhari reported: Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cVerily, faith consists of obligations, laws, limits, and traditions. Whoever perfects them has perfected faith, and whoever does not perfect them will not have perfect faith.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u